<br>
I've done some reading, and asked a few questions.  We were ready.<br>
<br>
Group was as follows:<br>
Wizard 31<br>
Warrior 33<br>
Ranger 34<br>
Druid 35<br>
<br>
I ***really*** wish we'd been able to get an enchanter.  Oh well.<br>
<br>
During the trip there were 3 deaths.  All mine.  The first was an act of stupidity on my part (I'll spare you the details).  The other 2 were the classic 'You Appear!' deaths.<br>
<br>
Because of were everyone was, we did it Sol A, Perma, Lake Rathe.  Ideally it would have been Perma, Lake Rathe, Sol A.  It would have saved travel time.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sol A:<br>
Hit EQAtlas and get a map.  You're heading to the bar (area 15 on EQAtlas).  You'll have to fight your way there.  It's not too bad.  The Gobs are located in small bunches.  <br>
<br>
Between the entrance, and the bar, we had 3 respectable fights (read, got exp), 1 minor one (no exp), and a couple straglers.  We where able to find a safe area and med up unmolested between each fight (with invis).<br>
<br>
Set up in the bar.  Get *behind* the bar.  The other Gobs won't agro if you stay behind the bar, and don't allow runners.  You'll be fine so long as you don't train any to yourself.<br>
<br>
The Inferno Goblin Wizard is a place holder for the Barkeep.  We got lucky.  The wizard was the second spawn.  We killed it.  I died just as the wizard did.  I ended up multiquesting this piece with the warrior.<br>
<br>
The irony is a lvl 50+ pali showed up 2 seconds after the loot wanting drakehide, and I got a revive (forgot to rebind, end up in Iceclad DOH!)  He got the camp as I ported us to Tox.  Very content.<br>
<br>
The warrior got the Fire Totem for her Crafted Helm while there, sweet!<br>
--<br>
<br>
Perma:<br>
Again, EQAtlas.  Your going to the jail.  Section 9.<br>
<br>
The fighting on the way there wasn't bad.  I did die from my invis dropping just as we got there.  Tanks couldn't help with 4 evokers nuking me.  They were barely scratched.<br>
<br>
I run in, get my corpse.  Loot, med, and picked a cell.<br>
<br>
We found one in the center of the 5 cells (as you look on the map).  Wizard was center at the rear of the room.  I'm sure he has a place holder, but was kind enough to drop the heart the first time.<br>
<br>
The 3rd death happend in a vain attempt to get the warrior an Icy Totem for her Crafted Boots.<br>
<br>
To NK<br>
--<br>
Lake Rathe:<br>
Easy!  The druid left at this point, but we were fine.<br>
<br>
From the Rathe Mountain zone, facing the lake, run along the left wall.  You'll find a pair of human casters (wizards??).  The skelies are in the tower (they con'd indif to me).<br>
<br>
Two Skels, blue to me at 30 (at this point=(.   Two pets, 1 blue 1 green.<br>
<br>
The ranger got a little cocky, and took a beating.  Got the rod, and were set.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
Then just run to the temple, turn in your Lambent Stone for the darkwood staff (if you haven't already), then find our quest giver.<br>
<br>
I had a lambent in storage for a while waiting for this, so I didn't include the time aquiring that in this figure.  They aren't tough to buy if anything else.<br>
<br>
I'd suggest walking through the prompts.<br>
<br>
It is a LARGE item.  I opted to get rid of an empty backpack and have an open main slot.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
I would not recommend you do this quest much below 30.  If you do, you will need a full group.  You WILL need an enchanter, and a cleric wouldn't hurt.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck.  I've had mine for a day, and love it.  I couldn't care less about the lost expierence, I like it that much.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now to quest those damn JBoots.<br>
<br>
